cn:listItem.cn:title: Securing Our Future: Cambridge Cyber Summit
cn:listItem.headline: The Cambridge Cyber Summit
cn:listItem.cn:summary: Top leaders from business, government and academia come together at the Cambridge Cyber Summit to address cyberthreats and secure America’s future.
cn:listItem.cn:shorterDescription: Top leaders from business, government and academia come together at the Cambridge Cyber Summit to address cyberthreats and secure America’s future.
cn:listItem.cn:shortestDescription: Top leaders from business, government and academia come together to address cyberthreats and secure America’s future.
cn:listItem.cn:bodyTeaser:
October 5, 2016

MIT Kresge Auditorium | 48 Massachusetts Ave. | Cambridge 02139

Register now for the Cambridge Cyber Summit

Share. Solve. Secure.

The Aspen Institute's Homeland Security Program, CNBC and MIT's Computer Science and Artificial Intelligence Lab (CSAIL) are partnering for the Cambridge Cyber Summit to find ways to combat urgent cyberthreats and secure America's future.

C-suite executives and business owners come together with public- and private-sector leaders in security, technology and defense, focusing on the next wave of cyberattacks and their perpetrators, countermeasures, privacy vs. security, the government's role in protecting private industry, and the latest trends in tech.

Featured speakers include:

  • Admiral Michael S. Rogers, Commander, U.S. Cyber Command; Director, National Security Agency; Chief, Central Security Service
  • Andrew McCabe, Deputy Director, Federal Bureau of Investigation
  • Thomas A. Fanning, President and CEO, Southern Company
  • Glenn Gerstell, General Counsel, National Security Agency
  • Dr. Tom Leighton, Co-founder, Akamai Technologies
  • Matt Olsen, Co-founder, IronNet Cybersecurity; former Director, National Counterterrorism Center

REGISTER NOW

image.caption: The Cambridge Cyber Summit at M.I.T.

cn:listItem.name: Securing Our Future: Cambridge Cyber Summit

cn:listItem.cn:title: Futures Now
cn:listItem.headline: Futures Now
cn:listItem.cn:summary: CNBC's "Futures Now," is the first multi-platform media experience entirely devoted to the futures market. Twice a week, in a fifteen-minute live program only available on CNBC.com, prominent traders focus on how to trade the news of the day using futures. From gold to gas to S&P, the "Futures Now" crew will teach you how to harness the power of the multi-trillion dollar futures market, and turn today's events into tomorrow's profits.
